<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bolgor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm the guild leader of a modest 50+ guild on Cazic Thule. We currently have about 20 members and I'm hoping to grow to about 30-40 in the near future. Prior to this guild, I was in 3 others, all of which I had incredible fun in, and made many long-lasting friendships. All of the split up, and now several good good friends of mine from these guilds are wanderring around guildless.<P>So I Target the 60 warriors first, and ask what their plans are. All of them reply similarly with I'm joining Uberguild "B". I ask why and they tell me, "I spent all this time getting to 60, and now I need to do the big raids." Uh-huh. So I start asking the others, all over 55, what their plans are...<BR>and I get "I'm joining Uberguild A, B, C, or D."(currently I'd say there are four guilds on CT that are above the rest, no I won't name them)<P>/sigh<P>Does nobody enjoy the little pleasures in life? The friends and the adventure? I may only be in a minor league guild but I still do someting new every week. and the things I've done for 3-4 mos now aren't that old, and I haven't seen every kind of loot drop, and I'm not fully equipped to want to proceed too far too fast.<P>Why do people need to beat the game thats unbeatable? Does anyone think they're gonna kill UberMob X and get a "Coongratulations, you Win!" Message? It seems to me that if you join an uberguild, and take out al the tough stuff and get everything done... Well, then what? All of these guys are the same ones who say, " I'm bored with Kael, I'm bored with Velks, I'm bored with blah blah blah." Do they think that TOV won't get boring? Or the Ssraa temple? <P>I don't want to go trudging off into the end game until I want to end the game. And if you're that tired of EQ just friggin quit. I'm feeling so left out when people say they're moving on to bigger and better things when I think what I'm doing is fun enough. Yes I want to see end-game bosses and such... but that can come later, slowly, when I'm ready. <P>Why does everyone else want to beat themselves up and leave all their friends behind just to see a boss mob, die to it, and not get any loot thats going to senior guild members?<P>I miss em all. <BR>/em sits in the corner rememberring better days<P>------------------<BR>Bolgor Brellwrath<BR>57 Dwarven Cleric of Brell Serillis<BR>Guild Leader of United Forsaken<BR>Cazic-Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Badany</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Some people still like smaller guilds, and I'm definately one of them!<P>We just did the Halls of Testing for the first time last night, and it was fantastic.  Yes to all the uber guilds on our server HoT is cake for them, and they are bored of it.  Fine by me I say!<P>First night out and I got Plate boots woot!<P>I think we are still considered a small guild.  Take a look at our member listing:<P>*feanan 60 druid<BR>caiffena 56 druid<BR>jiggly 54 druid<BR>meeffas 53 druid<BR>blondx 53 druid<BR>aldur 52 druid - alt<P>*thud 60 warrior<BR>jakmode 59 warrior<BR>diminous 56 warrior<BR>aldurson 56 warrior<BR>wareden 52 warrior<BR>laann < 50 warrior<BR>aallain 56 warrior - alt<BR>starina 54 warrior - alt<P>*tietan 60 cleric <BR>*semirahge 60 cleric<BR>edrob 60 cleric<BR>sampoerna 56 cleric<BR>*hamyr 55 cleric<BR>*badany 55 cleric<BR>homegrown 53 cleric<BR>meka 52 cleric<BR>mollica 52 cleric<BR>elof 51 Cleric<BR>oiciggy <50 cleric<BR>fvanilla <50 cleric<P>*essej 60 enchanter<BR>*sendara 59 enchanter<BR>neybious 54 enchanter<BR>yumiko 60 enchanter - alt<BR>mindtap 48 enchanter - alt<P>*razatian 60 ranger<BR>*llerian 58 ranger<BR>eholli 56 ranger<P>draiden 52 wizard -alt<P>*hallad 59 rogue<BR>*ewben 60 rogue<BR>*sammuel 59 rogue<BR>*krizzyn 55 rogue<BR>bergle <50 rogue<P>woadin 58 shaman<BR>fionnabhair 55 shaman<BR>nels 52 shaman<BR>zkrydack 49 shaman - alt<P>cereborn 59 necro<BR>cricket 57 necro<BR>ignaciio 56 necro - alt<P>nalaht 56 mage<BR>pneladobaryn 54 mage<BR>nave 54 mage<P>evilseed 57 shadow knight<BR>grundall 53 shadow knight<BR>zahr 52 shadow knight<P>*maomao 60 monk<BR>*ariyel 58 monk<P>faealron 55 pally<BR>rayman 52 pally<BR>thalan 56 pally - alt<P>* = epic <P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28272" TARGET=_blank>Badany Greatheal</A><BR>Templar of the Prime Healer Rodcet Nife<BR>Zebuxoruk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">piikaa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am following a similar thread on the Defender's of the Realm web-site.  They have a member that wants to join an UberGuild, and it discusses how everyone is handling it.  Makes for a pretty interesting read.<BR> <A HREF="http://dor.proboards2.com/index.cgi?pbuser=dor&board=general&action=display&num=1011198611" TARGET=_blank>http://dor.proboards2.com/index.cgi?pbuser=dor&board=general&action=display&num=1011198611</A> <P>This (Piikaa)is my only character and I have been active in a small guild with mid-level players.  I really like the fact that we are more of a "help each other out" club, than a bunch of regimented soldiers, out to kill the best and brightest MOB's VI can build.  I think it is more challenging and rewarding to be able to play solo or join a random pick-up group when I feel like playing.  I also like the fact that we also will group up and go somewhere (place and purpose trips) as a group of guild members.<P>I played RPG's for many years and this game is the closest I have found to the fun and interaction that I enjoyed from D&D.  I admit, when I joined the guild, I thought I would hang out until I was ready for a 50+ guild invite.  Now, I think I will really enjoy giving back to others in my guild when I reach that higher level.  There are more rewarding aspects to this game than just getting more plat & some "great weapon".<P>Piikaa Fishweed<BR>31st Drunken Dwarven Battlecleric of Brell<BR>(Proud member of Twilight Order)<BR>Bertoxxulous Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Twinskey Bab0linskey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">EQ's open way of playing allows people of very differnt motivations and styles of enjoy playing the same game.  Why shouldn't the appeal of big mob's and phat lewt draw some people?  <P>If your not ready, then enjoy what it is you enjoy... other people are always going to do what it is they enjoy.  If you don't plan on raiding, then size of guild is un-important.<P>If what you want is to lead a sizeable force of raiders, start by doing what you can... plane's raids, epics, DN, WW, Kael, Thurg whatever you can handle and invite outsider's around level 54-56.  Every place I mentioned can be done with a small amount of people, and outsider's will want to join when they see you do raid/get good stuff.<P>The high end game lacks good leaders more then good players.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nemean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Badany, that is NOT a small guild by any measure.  Our guild has about 30 regulars, so if we have a raid where 4 groups turn up, we are happy.  Having said that, we raid HoT regularly, we've started doing the NToV mobs (only the easy guys).  Admittedly with 2 groups of friends we did Vindi the other day.  And I think you guys have a far more formidable guild than us.<P>Size is not everything in EQ.  Unless you want to Zerg everything, 4 groups of high level, reasonably well equipped people who know what they're doing, will do a lot more than 7 groups of idiots.  I know, I've been on both types of raids.... </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Phalia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">A little off topic, but would someone please explain zerging to me.  I see the phrase all the time.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Siren</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>A little off topic, but would someone please explain zerging to me. I see the phrase all the time.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>Zerging is when you take well over the amount of players necessary to kill a mob, using bum rush and/or bind rush tactics and hurl yourself skill-lessly at a mob. <P>Zergling guilds tend to have 100+ members and travel in swarms. =P<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Does nobody enjoy the little pleasures in life? The friends and the adventure? I may only be in a minor league guild but I still do someting new every week<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>IMO the guild's that work best are the guilds that are made up of like minded people.  When others with similar philosophy as you see that your guild is doing new things each week, they may be prompted to seek membership.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Sirensa the Vicar <BR><A HREF="http://hossguild.com" TARGET=_blank>Hoss</A><BR>Druzzil Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nemean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Phalia:<BR><B>A little off topic, but would someone please explain zerging to me.  I see the phrase all the time.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Siren explained it well - just adding that the name comes from Starcraft.  In there one of the races were called Zerg - and their main battle technique was to built many many cheap units, and hurl them at the enemy, until weight of numbers won them the battle.  Thats where the name comes from.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Phalia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">hehe Thank you kindly  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Esmecat</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">LOL couldn't believe it when i saw that term. my husband is a startcraft fanatic... <P>basicly it is like cannonfodder... lol. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Badany</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Nemean:<BR><B>Badany, that is NOT a small guild by any measure.  Our guild has about 30 regulars, </B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>OK, so you have 30 members and you are a small guild, but we have 49 members (subtracting alts) and we are not a small guild?<P>Hehe.  Well we usually only have about 15 people online at peak times, 49 total members.  Some of those people aren't active any more either, I think a handful have switched over to DAoC.<P><P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28272" TARGET=_blank>Badany Greatheal</A><BR>Templar of the Prime Healer Rodcet Nife<BR>Zebuxoruk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aladain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What irks me is...<P>When a guild gets called a zergling guild because they do everything in high numbers, but the reality is that they do everything in high numbers because they enjoy each others company.  My guild is the largest guild on Tholuxe member-wise (157 members last count).  When we do like kael arena mobs to stock up on some armor, or something, we have 30-35 people.  Sure, we can do it single-group np, but no one really wants to.  Would prefer to have the company of the entire guild with us to condradulate everyone on victory.<P>Why would I be considered zergling, and why would anyone care anyway?  Not like it affects them.<P>Aladain<p>[This message has been edited by Aladain (edited 01-18-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Feias</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I wouldn't call that zerging them.<P>Personally it I would consider zerging a mob when doing a mob or set of mobs requires that many people.  When I was in kael the other day there was a guild of about 40 in there gathering armor and not one of them was over 52.  They had multiple whipouts and very little chance for individual armor.  They required the presence of everyone there in order to even remain a viable force.<P>I don't think this is bad but it does fall under the category of zerging something.  When you bring 40 people to a mob where only 6 are needed you really just have observers or an overabundance of bodies.<P>I do agree it is fun and the most fun I have is when we have a large portion of my guild together talking and beating stuff down.  Fun aside, the problem comes in when a guild that is incapable of successfully downing a mob decides to rely on numbers instead of skill, levels, or tactics.  This is when bad stuff happens.<P>When you see a large number of 46 to 50s tagging along with a few 50+ in HoT there can only be trouble and a CR to follow.<p>[This message has been edited by Feias (edited 01-18-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nemean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Badany:<BR><B> Hehe.  Well we usually only have about 15 people online at peak times, 49 